cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with real-time human performance capture from monocular video using deep neural networks and dense photometric and silhouette constraints. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with capturing dense, space-time coherent deforming geometry of entire humans in general everyday clothing. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with real-time capture of human performance from video. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper deals with tracking non-rigid deformations of skin and apparel using a novel real-time capable algorithm. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper deals with capturing human performance in real-time, which could have applications in human-computer interaction.
